DO -WHILE ➖
—---------------------
Do while loop is  a exit controlled loop.
 When we dont know the number of iterations and atleast once wants to execute then we have to use do while loop.
Syntax ➖-

Do{
// statement
}
while(condition);


Ex:-
—-
class Demo
{
public static void main(String []args)
{
int a =1;
do{
System.out.println(" ee sala cup namdu");
}
while(a>5);
 }
}

Op:- 
Ee sala cup namdu

NOTE:-
—--------
 In the above programme condition is false .  so we are getting output one time
 Because  if condition false so do while loop print the statement once .
